{
  "stem": "20686.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They couldn't understand that Shakespeare was a-- a matter of fact when I came to Australia, and somebody wanted to sort of intimidate me, on the account of Yiddish speaking.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I said to him, look, I was very pleasantly surprised when I came to Australia, and I found that Shakespeare is translated in English, too.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He looked at me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He gave me a funny look.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I said, yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I read Shakespeare in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He would not-- could not-- but we had it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We had Shakespeare, and [INAUDIBLE], and Kafka, and-- and-- and Flaubert.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And you name it, and Balzac, we had it all in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And most probably the children of my vintage, young boys and girls, were by 16 or 17 years a-- completely acquainted with the Russian and French classics.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had Pushkin, and Chekhov, and Turgenev, and-- and Tolstoy, and Dostoyevsky, and Flaubert and Balzac, and-- and Victor Hugo.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We read them all.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We knew them all.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We spoke Yiddish at home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yiddish was the major language.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But my sisters also spoke Polish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] After all, we-- Polish was part of-- of-- you know, it was the language of the country.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Polish was spoken, but not to the extent that we-- one could say that we linguistic-- were we linguistically assimilated?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was in a factory owned by Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was-- there were Germans, and Poles, and Ukrainians.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a matter of fact, my father was their delegate, their delegate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was delegated from the workers to negotiate with the-- with the boss about the conditions and so on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was not an exclusive Yiddish factory just-- just for Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was a-- a-- a Bundist.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was active in the professional and in the textile movement.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
